This is a somewhat random idea based on the interviews I've seen people do. Does anyone have a question for any one of my characters? (Can be MOO characters, can be chat characters, whatever.) They'll do their best to answer. If anyone else would like one of their characters interviewed, then drop a comment for that too.

So . . . all character questions and requests for questions, please drop a comment.

. . . Come on. You know you want to. ^^;;;

Isis needed people to go with her to a talk on global warming tonight, so I said I'd go.  Oi.  I didn't think I'd be staying the whole time.  o.o  Well, I did . . . and twas interesting -- a bit.  It turned out to be a debate between two presenters.  The first one was mild, softer-spoken, and honestly rather boring in his presentation, although I think his facts were better and the whole presentation was better put together.  The points he argued were clear and concise from my point of view, each flowing into the other smoothly.  The other man, however, was certainly livelier, yet he jumped from subject to subject, speaking very quickly.  He was ostentatious both in manner and the "politeness" he deferred to his colleague.

Rather funny, though, at the end they were allowed to rebut one another's arguments.  The first man makes a statement . . . something about not taking into account the effects of the errupting volcanoes on the rising temperatures . . . the other man goes "WHAT????!" and leaps from his seat to start showing slides of his own!  I thought he was going to go for the first presenter's throat!  o.o  And then they engaged in verbal sparring with one another, rather openly insulting each other as they feigned politeness!  lol . . . Society can be so funny at times . . .  :)

Ara, in other news, my computer continues to concoct plots to get me.  Now it goes into hibernation and won't turn back on again *while* I have documents on the screen.  Grrrrr . . . Can I fire it?  --;
